title: Power Play Goals Lead 'Dogs to Rivalry Win
text:
Power Play Goals Lead 'Dogs to Rivalry Win 
By Zach Schneider Power Play Goals Lead 'Dogs to Rivalry Win October 16, 2015 Updated Oct 16, 2015 at 9:27 PM CDT 
Minneapolis, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Jared Thomas and Austin Farley scored power play goals in the second period on Friday night en route to the No. 7 University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team getting a 3-1 win over No. 15 Minnesota at Mariucci Arena. 
Those goals came late in the second period and put UMD up 2-0, with Farley's marking his eighth career goal against the Gophers. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
After Brent Gates, Jr. made it 2-1 early in the third, period, Dominic Toninato scored on his own rebound less than two minutes later to account for the 3-1 final score. 
Kasimir Kaskisuo made 23 saves to earn the win for UMD, which has now won a program record five straight games against Minnesota. 
The series now shifts to AMSOIL Arena on Saturday night, with faceoff scheduled for 7:07 p.m.
